<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="88" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 18643/13.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Dudley</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-16"><hi rend="italic">January 16,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Ambassador Dudley reports that Brazil has granted to the United States a
                            differential tariff reduction of 20 per cent during 1910 on 11 articles
                            which were so favored in 1909, and which will be construed to include
                            alarm clocks, and in addition cement, desks, dried fruit, school
                            furniture, and corsets.</p>
                    </div>
